<h3 style='margin-top:.1pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:.1pt;margin-left:
0in'><a name=describe><i style='mso-bidi-font-style:normal'><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Description </span></i></a><i
style='mso-bidi-font-style:normal'><span style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><o:p></o:p></span></i></h3>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:.1pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:.1pt;
margin-left:0in'><span style='font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>This
workshop aims to bring together researchers and designers from academia and
industry to discuss directions in the development of high-performance,
parallel, and distributed processors and systems. The main goal of the workshop
is to discuss future trends in the development of architecture and software
systems and to explore the assumptions made by the architects about software
systems and by software writers about architecture. The increased complexity in
each of these areas calls for increased interaction with researchers from all
of the other disciplines to accurately assess the potential directions and
future trends in architecture and systems. The topics of interest include, but
are not limited, to the following:<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<ul style='margin-top:0in' type=disc>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;mso-pagination:none;mso-list:
     l0 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:
     none'><i style='mso-bidi-font-style:normal'><span style='font-size:11.0pt;
     font-family:"Arial",sans-serif'>Multi- and Many-core processors<o:p></o:p></span></i></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;mso-pagination:none;mso-list:
     l0 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:
     none'><i style='mso-bidi-font-style:normal'><span style='font-size:11.0pt;
     font-family:"Arial",sans-serif'>Heterogeneous computing<o:p></o:p></span></i></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;mso-pagination:none;mso-list:
     l0 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:
     none'><i style='mso-bidi-font-style:normal'><span style='font-size:11.0pt;
     font-family:"Arial",sans-serif'>Memory technology and system organization<o:p></o:p></span></i></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;mso-pagination:none;mso-list:
     l0 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:
     none'><i style='mso-bidi-font-style:normal'><span style='font-size:11.0pt;
     font-family:"Arial",sans-serif'>Software- and technology-driven and
     constrained new architectures<o:p></o:p></span></i></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;mso-pagination:none;mso-list:
     l0 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:
     none'><i style='mso-bidi-font-style:normal'><span style='font-size:11.0pt;
     font-family:"Arial",sans-serif'>Applications and their performance<o:p></o:p></span></i></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;mso-pagination:none;mso-list:

     none'><i style='mso-bidi-font-style:normal'><span style='font-size:11.0pt;
     font-family:"Arial",sans-serif'>Power management<o:p></o:p></span></i></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;mso-pagination:none;mso-list:
     l0 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:
     none'><i style='mso-bidi-font-style:normal'><span style='font-size:11.0pt;
     font-family:"Arial",sans-serif'>Compiler/architecture interaction and

 <li class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;mso-pagination:none;mso-list:
